Package cmpt355.project.codegen

Class Label

java.lang.Object
cmpt355.project.jvm.Operand
cmpt355.project.jvm.InstructionAddressOperand
cmpt355.project.codegen.Label
public class Label
extends InstructionAddressOperand
A class representing a label in assembly code: something that can be branched by to another instruction such as Instruction.new_goto(InstructionAddressOperand). A label must have its mark() method called at the point that the label is to branch to. For example, in code like 

     context.addCode(/* instruction A */);
     label.mark();
     context.addCode(/* instruction B */);
a branch to label would execute instruction B next.

      public void mark()
      Marks the label at this particular point in the code. If this method is not called on a label before the assembly file is to be generated, an exception will be thrown at that time.
